dismissalComment.html: what a catch!! athleticism at its best! that was a good length delivery from Pathan, Chanderpaul has a swing at it, doesn't keep the ball down, the ball dies as it reaches Sehwag who is positioned on the fence, but he makes good ground, and times his dive forward to perfection, pouches the ball neatly and comes up with the ball

dismissalComment.html: driven down to long-off, take the first run quickly and think about the second, Samuels takes off for the second run, but Baugh is not too impressed, holds his ground at the striker's end, the fielder at long-off fires in a perfect throw back to Pathan who is up at the stumps, and Pathan duly whips off the bails, its bye-bye for Samuels

dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag run out (Samuels/†Baugh) 22 (32b 3x4 0x6 51m) SR: 68.75

dismissalComment.html: Gone! got his man! bit bizaare actually! First Sehwag goes for a wild heave over the bowler but only manages to send the ball in a orbit up over mid-off, where Marlon samuels misjudges it as he goes back and doesn't get a hand on it. But here is where the Indians helped. They turn for the second run, rather Dravid comes back without any hesitation but Sehwag, who is caught ball watching, is late to get off  and fails to reach the crease in time. Samuels had fired the throw straight to the keeper who took off the bails in a flash. It should have been a comfortable two, if Sehwag had not been ball watching.

commentTextItems.html: That's it! game over! Kaif slams a full-length delivery, just outside the off stump, through the covers and finds the fence! India register their 17th successful run chase on the trot.

commentPostTextItems.html: Powered by serene hundred by Rahul Dravid and a vital 66 from Mohammad Kaif, who finally ended his run-drought, India registered their 17th  successful run-chase in a row. West Indies had their chances but their poor fielding let them down and proved costly in the end. Dravid's efforts won him the man of the match award. The second ODI match will be played on Saturday May 20, do join us then. This is Sriram Veera, along with Sajan Nair, signing off. Good bye and Good luck!

commentTextItems.html: almost a runout! drives straight to Lara at midwicket who hurls it to the non-strikers' end but Bravo doesn't attempt to take the throw, thinks it will hit the stump straight, it doesn't and they miss a runout
short of length, on the stumps, swatted away to deep midwicket. Raina on the strike now. Here we go!
Tension mounts now! Kaif hits straight to Lara at covers again! what drama here!

commentPreTextItems.html: Lara has a lengthy talk with Bravo, who will bowl the last over, on the field settings. Just four people in the circle.

commentTextItems.html: yorker length on the off stump, driven to cover
yorker length, on the leg stump, dug out to long on. So just four runs needed now.  should be easy for India but ...

commentTextItems.html: on the pads, turned past midwicket for a comfortable couple of runs. Only 5 more needed for India now
on a length, outside the off stump, driven to long-off. 7 off 8
short of length, around the off stump, pushed to cover, where Lara fields and has a shy at non-strikers end and if he had hit Kaif would have been dead
pushed across, yorker length and Raina tries to run it down to third man, misses
edge and a four! slash outside the off stump and it flies to the third man fence, Just 8 runs now,
oh! Lucky Kaif! has a almighty heave to a full-length delivery, outside the off stump but it falls between the long-on fielder running in and Lara who runs from covers

commentTextItems.html: oh! almost a chance! Kaif has a go at a full length delivery outside the off stump and the outside edge sends the ball flying to the right of a diving Baugh. That four changes it all - just 14 required now from 13 balls

commentTextItems.html: gone! Game on folks! Full-length delivery on the middle stump, Dhoni again takes his left foot just outside the line and whacks it towards long-on. It flew straight to the fielder there. Don't go anywhere!
Yes Sir! a four! Attempted yorker turned into a low full toss. Dhoni gets his left foot out of the line, outside the leg stump and thumps it to deep midwicket
a mis-field results in a run! full toss and driven straight to Sarwan at point, who fumbles. Dhoni on strike now! Here we go!
Ah! just a run. full and angling intowards the pads, Kaif has a flash, misses and it runs to short third man for a run

commentPostTextItems.html: Wonderful over from Jerome Taylor there. The Squeeze is on!

dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag run out (Samuels/†Baugh) 22 (32b 3x4 0x6 51m) SR: 68.75

dismissalComment.html: Gone! got his man! bit bizaare actually! First Sehwag goes for a wild heave over the bowler but only manages to send the ball in a orbit up over mid-off, where Marlon samuels misjudges it as he goes back and doesn't get a hand on it. But here is where the Indians helped. They turn for the second run, rather Dravid comes back without any hesitation but Sehwag, who is caught ball watching, is late to get off  and fails to reach the crease in time. Samuels had fired the throw straight to the keeper who took off the bails in a flash. It should have been a comfortable two, if Sehwag had not been ball watching.
